tracks: 1 Solomon, HWV 67: Arrival Of The Queen Of Sheba, 2 Water Music Suite No.1 In F, HWV 348: 8. Hornpipe, 3 Water Music, Suites 2 & 3 In D/G, HWV 348: 6. Bourrée, 4 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 1.Symphony, 5 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 2. "Comfort ye, My people", 6 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 3. "Ev'ry Valley shall be exalted", 7 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 4. "And The Glory Of The Lord", 8 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 5. "Thus saith the Lord", 9 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 6. "But who may abide the day of his coming", 10 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 7. "And He shall purify the sons of Levi", 11 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 8. "Behold, a virgin shall conceive", 12 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 9. "O thou that tellest good tidings to Zion", 13 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 10. "For behold, darkness shall cover", 14 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 11. "The people that walked in darkness", 15 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 12. "For unto us a Child is born", 16 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 13. "Pifa (Pastoral Symphony)", 17 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 14. "There were shepherds ... And suddenly there", 18 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 15. "Glory to God in the highest", 19 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 16. "Rejoice greatly, o daughter of Zion", 20 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 17a. "Then shall the eyes of the blind", 21 Messiah / Part 1: 18a. "He shall feed his flock", 22 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 1: 19. "His yoke is easy", 23 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 20. "Behold the Lamb of God", 24 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 21. "He was despised", 25 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 22. "Surely He hath borne our griefs", 26 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 23. "And with His stripes we are healed", 27 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 24. "All we like sheep have gone astray", 28 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 25. "All they that see Him", 29 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 26. "He trusted in God", 30 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 27. "Thy rebuke hath broken His heart", 31 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 28. "Behold and see", 32 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 29. "He was cut off", 33 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 30. "But thou didst not leave", 34 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 31. "Lift up your heads", 35 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 32. "Unto which of the angels", 36 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 33. "Let all the angels of God", 37 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 34a. "Thou art gone up on high", 38 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 35. "The Lord gave the word", 39 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 36. "How beautiful are the feet", 40 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 37a. "Their sound is gone out", 41 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 38. "Why do the nations so furiously rage together?", 42 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 39. "Let us break their bonds asunder", 43 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 40. "He that dwelleth in heaven", 44 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 41. "Thou shalt break them", 45 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 2: 42. "Hallelujah", 46 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 3: 43. "I know that my Redeemer liveth", 47 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 3: 44. "Since by man came death", 48 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 3: 45. "Behold, I tell you a mystery", 49 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 3: 46. "The trumpet shall sound", 50 Messiah, HWV 56 / Pt. 3: 47. "Then shall be brought to pass"
